\paragraph{Common settings.} All experiments use Stable Diffusion v1.4 with 50 DDIM steps, CFG scale $s{=}7.5$, seed 42, and $512{\times}512$ resolution. CLIP exemplar embeddings are computed with ViT-L/14 from $F\cdot K{=}16$ images per concept. Cross-attention is read at resolutions $16{\times}16$ and $32{\times}32$. Sigmoid sharpness $\alpha{=}10.0$ and mask blur $\sigma{=}1.0$ are fixed.

\paragraph{Pattern.} The per-concept configuration follows a consistent logic (previewed in \S\ref{subsec:training_free}): probe choice tracks concept--prompt alignment (text for lexically identifiable concepts, image for metaphorically described ones, both when they contribute non-redundantly); the How-mode scale follows mode by construction ($s_\text{h}$ is roughly $10{\times}s_\text{a}$ because the two-direction difference $d^{\text{anc}}_f - d^{\text{tgt}}_f$ partially cancels); $\tau$ tracks family-alignment signal magnitude (internally coherent concepts such as nudity produce high-magnitude alignment so $\tau{=}0.6$ filters benign prompts reliably, while semantically dispersed concepts (violence, harassment, hate) use $\tau{=}0.4$ to avoid missed triggers).

\subsection{Generation Pipeline (per DDIM step)}
\label{app:pipeline}

At every step $t$ of the 50-step DDIM process, \ours{} runs:
\begin{enumerate}[leftmargin=1.5em,itemsep=1pt]
    \item Compute $\epsilon_\varnothing$, $\epsilon_\theta(z_t, c)$, and $\{\epsilon_\theta(z_t, c^{\text{tgt}}_{f,k})\}_{f,k}$ (batched; the family mean is reused).
    \item Evaluate $\text{CAS}(t)$ (Eq.~\ref{eq:cas}); if $\text{CAS}(t) < \tau$ and the sticky latch is off, skip guidance.
    \item Extract family-level cross-attention maps $\{M^f_\text{text}\}$ (Eq.~\ref{eq:text_probe}).
    \item Score intermediate U-Net features against $\{\bar{e}_f\}$ to form $\{M^f_\text{img}\}$ (Eq.~\ref{eq:img_probe}).
    \item Fuse across families and modalities (Eq.~\ref{eq:fusion}) to obtain $M$.
    \item Apply anchor inpainting (Eq.~\ref{eq:anchor_inpaint}) or hybrid guidance (Eq.~\ref{eq:hybrid}).
\end{enumerate}
The overhead per step is $\approx 15$--$20\%$ over standard CFG, dominated by the extra UNet forward pass for the family-averaged target prediction and by CLIP feature extraction.

